<br>
Lately, it seems to me like warrior taunt is really subpar compared to knight taunt abilities. What it boils down to is, with a sk/pal tank the slower can slow the mob as soon as it's in camp, whereas with a warrior they have to wait 5-10 seconds, or even until I land my ch.<br>
<br>
It's a difference of 1 ch for a knight per fight versus 2 for the warrior, which negates the warrior hp advantage as far as healer mana is concerned - especially coupled with the fact that there's less margin for error with a warrior tank for the casters, who often pull taunt off him and need additional heals.<br>
<br>
I seriously think warrior taunt needs an upgrade, and came here to ask if one is in the works, and when is it going live. I mean, right now, as a cleric in PoP I actually prefer a knight tank to a warrior. In PoD at a few nights ago, we had a 58 warrior and a 55 sk in the group, and when we made the sk tank and relegated the warrior to a support role, we actually managed to pull faster! What the hell is that. Not right.<br>
<br>
Deian<br>
59 Cleric<br>
