<br>
Speaking of Hybrid/Knight taunt vs Warrior taunt which class do you find your guilds relying more on in PoP?<br>
<br>
When clearing to the bosses we use knights as main tank. When fighting most bosses we also use knights as main tank. Very rarely do we even put our warriors in the tank rotation for Drunder clearings up to and including Rallos Zek, Trials in Halls of Honor, Aerin'Dar, Behemoth, Saryn, or anything else other than Bertoxx any more, and even durring the Bertoxx encounter we still only use warriors as the tanks only after we've exausted our supply of knights for the kings and other assorted named. <br>
<br>
Our warriors end up doing nothing during these encounters and I think alot of us feel like we're getting the shaft. Maybe it's just my guild that has placed such importance on the use of Knights and their all-too-powerful aggro control methods, but our warriors have the best eb weapons availible, we have all the required AA abilities, all the right gear. We have 9k+ warriors but we still end up using Knights who match and even surpass the majority of our tanks hitpoints, which can be another thread all on it's own.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Taunt works fine. If there is something wrong it's that Knight's taunt is too good and needs to be nerfed some not the other way around.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I agree with this statement, I don't feel our mob control is insufficient, but I feel that knights are too far over powered in comparrison, and we are left with no way to compete. They can have superior AC and HP(we have knights in the upper 8k's while the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>majority</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of our warriors don't even meet this number), but giving them superior Taunt is going too far. It's bad enough their Elemental armors are only 15hp less than ours, in addition to giving hundreds of mana while giving us nothing else to balance out the difference, but to make them better at everything else we can do for our guild at an encounter is dissapointing.<br>
<br>
Why even have warriors in Everquest? The only difference between the two of us is that they get a complete array of heals, group heals, buffs, cures, stuns and so on and so on, and we get.... defensive and shield. Wow.<br>
<br>
