My guild uses warriors as tanks so Im happy but I do see more and more pally / sks outaggroing me and it makes me wonder what good I am for. Most sk / pal get better dmg weapon then us, most sk / pal get the same if not higher hp then us since they got better aggro, they also get equipped first. Like the above poster said, elemental armor they have same stats str / sta /dex about, they got 35 less hp but got 100 mana added to that. When VI designed epic, to balance them, they did well having x number of stats for everyone and x number of mana + hp. So if they get all mana they dont get hp, if they get more mana, they get less hp.<br>
<br>
Imo, easy way to make us back into our True role is getting rid of all aggro on spells like stun, SK snare, and some other spells. Problem then is that necros / clerics have same spells, so they wont get aggro when casting their spells which is not good either. The problem is nerfing aggro is good for warriors but not good for the general idea since sks would get better at same time which might not be intended by VI.<br>
<br>
Atm it is :<br>
<br>
Pal / SK have advantages War dont have, spells, they can heal / lifetap, root / snare, buff up, CH / HT, etc etc<br>
<br>
Pal / SK have same hp / ac as War in the high end game<br>
<br>
Pal / SK 1hand / 2hander sometimes outdmg warriors<br>
<br>
Pal / SK can out aggro War<br>
<br>
Pal / SK is now MT when it was designed that War was the MT.<br>
<br>
<br>
there are ways to fix taunt, needs some reflection, but I do agree, atm, in high end game the real only advantage of tanks is a disc usable every 10min (a bit less) which is defensive so you only need a warrior every 10min to tank a mob while you should need him 100percent of time for all tanking job. And that is only when you really do require defensive which you now rarely do. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
