<br>
Most warriors dont have any problems maintaining aggro over the long duration.  Its getting the aggro early and holding it through debuffs/slows/early ch's etc that is the issue.<br>
<br>
Warriors are dependant on procs (i.e. flat out luck) to get and hold aggro early.  We give up dmg for no dmg procs to do our job because every other class in the game can taunt better then we do (even if they dont want to, they can).<br>
<br>
I agree a war and pal in = equipment, war will always have more hp and in most cases more ac.  The issue is when both equipped with top end gear have a diff of 500 hp, negligible difference in ac,  and one class can lock aggro down from the word go and hold the duration... which do you want to use?<br>
