<br>
What if they already trivialized aggro management?<br>
<br>
What if there was a class that could hold aggro even through early heals, slows and debuffs?<br>
<br>
What if there were two classes that did this?<br>
<br>
What if these classes wore platemail armor. And had a taunt button as well?<br>
<br>
What if they even had a skill that allowed them to bash through their 2hander, no matter what race they chose?<br>
<br>
What if, because of these things they could hold aggro almost seamlessly?<br>
<br>
If this were the case, then, wouldn't every warrior who says &quot;If they fixed taunt, the encounters would be trivial&quot; be missing the fact that the encounters already are trivialized by knight ability to hold and maintain aggro?<br>
<br>
Just some questions I've had floating around in my head ever since I grouped with a 61 pally in PoN who could hold aggro 10 times better than any one of my trio of warrior friends.<br>
<br>
And since I'm a monk, I don't like getting crunched by mobs too much these days. So I rather liked not having to evade much with a pally tank.<br>
